Now lets subset the cow data that contains the data sources, the admin location, the treatment and the yield values

data_subset <- cow_data[,c(2,3,6,9, 17,19, 25:28, 40)]

Columns of the subseted data

colnames(data_subset)
##  [1] "Point_X"               "Point_Y"               "Data..Source.Lineage."

##  [7] "N..kg.ha."             "P...kg.ha."            "K..kg.ha."            
## [10] "S...kg.ha."            "Grain.yield.kg.ha."

Now let’s change the column names for better readability

colnames(data_subset) <- c("long", "lat", "source","region", "crop", 
                           "year", "n", "p", "k", "s", "grain_yield")
data_subset <- data_subset |> mutate(crop = tolower(crop))

pts = st_as_sf(data_subset, coords = c("long", "lat"), crs = "EPSG:4326")
